h3. What problem are you facing?

When using a generic type, the type of `Filter` seems to break down. This seems to be isolated to when using a generic type, as "hardcoding" the type works fine.
h3. What driver and relevant dependency versions are you using?

"mongodb": "4.7.0"

"typescript": "4.6.4"
h3. Steps to reproduce?
{code:java}
async function demo<T extends { foo: string }>() {
    const client = await MongoClient.connect('mongodb://xyz');

    const col = client.db().collection<T>('foo');
    col.findOne({ foo: 'foo' });
}{code}
Results in
{code:java}
TS2769: No overload matches this call.   The last overload gave the following error.     Argument of type '{ foo: "foo"; }' is not assignable to parameter of type 'Filter<T>'.       Type '{ foo: "foo"; }' is not assignable to type '{ [Property in Join<NestedPaths<WithId<T>>, ".">]?: Condition<PropertyType<WithId<T>, Property>> | undefined; } & RootFilterOperators<...>'.         Type '{ foo: "foo"; }' is not assignable to type '{ [Property in Join<NestedPaths<WithId<T>>, ".">]?: Condition<PropertyType<WithId<T>, Property>> | undefined; }'.{code}
Whereas "hardcoding" the type works fine
{code:java}
async function demo<>() {
    const client = await MongoClient.connect('mongodb://xyz');

    const col = client.db().collection<{ foo: string }>('foo');
    col.findOne({ foo: 'foo' });
}{code}
Oddly enough, autocomplete seems to provide the correct type for "foo":
!image-2022-06-14-14-22-52-539.png!

Raising this ticket specifically for the error raised when an invalid {{compressor}} is supplied, however it may be beneficial to align all connection parsing errors in a similar fashion.

For example, in the [3.6 Driver|https://github.com/mongodb/node-mongodb-native/blob/3.6/lib/core/uri_parser.js#L265] the error is:

{code}
throw new MongoParseError(
        'Value for `compressors` must be at least one of: `snappy`, `zlib`'
      );
{code}

whereas in the [4.0 Driver|https://github.com/mongodb/node-mongodb-native/blob/4.0/src/connection_string.ts#L598-L608] the error is:

{code}
throw new MongoParseError(`${c} is not a valid compression mechanism`);
{code}

Ideally these errors would consistently include both:
* the invalid value that was passed
* the list of accepted values (where appropriate)

